I have officially solved the greatest mystery in all Owl City history A few years ago, when I was 7, my dad had an Apple Music account and I used to add songs to my library and change the Metadata to be completely different. Two songs I did them to I changed the artist to "Minecraft", changed the album art to a stock image of Judy from Zootopia for whatever reason, and changed one of the songs titles. The two files were "12. Bombshell Blonde.m4p" and "01. Minecraft.m4p", the mystery was trying to figure out which song "01. Minecraft.m4p" was. I used kid3 to look at the Metadata, I was able to deduce from the Album ID and the Copyright Date that it was a song from TMS. And after using the catalog ID to find the song, I found it to be "Gold" So, mystery solved, "01. Minecraft.m4p", the mysterious Metadata changed song from 2016 when I was 7, turned out to be "Gold" (And if you're wondering why I didn't just play the audio file, it had Apple Music DRM tied to my dad's old Apple Music account, so I couldn't play it even if I wanted to)
